The paper deals with deep neural networks and their optimization, which are typically studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) communities. The paper also discusses the use of batch normalization, which is a popular technique in neural network optimization and is often studied in the neural networks (cs.NE) community. The paper proposes a new optimization method that involves constraining the filters to lie on a unit-norm manifold, which is a technique that is often used in optimization problems in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data science (cs.DS).
